      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">37.601</ph> General.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2402e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2424e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            Solicitations may use either a performance work statement or a statement of objectives (see <xref href="37.602.dita#FAR_37_602"
                        base="i1077411"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">37.602</xref>).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2424e18" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            Performance-based contracts for services shall include-</p>
               <ol id="d2402e35" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2424e24" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
								                A performance work statement (PWS);</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2424e29" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
								                Measurable performance standards (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">i.e.,</i> in terms of quality, timeliness, quantity, etc.) and the method of assessing contractor performance against performance standards; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2424e37" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
								                Performance incentives where appropriate. When used, the performance incentives shall correspond to the performance standards set forth in the contract (see <xref href="16.402-2.dita#FAR_16_402_2"
                              base="i1104460"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">16.402-2</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2424e45" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
						            See <xref href="12.102.dita#FAR_12_102"
                        base="i1113668"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">12.102</xref>(g) for the use of <xref href="Part_12.dita#FAR_Part_12"
                        base="i1113784"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">partÂ  12</xref> procedures for performance-based acquisitions.</p>
